    Or perhaps a warrior using /disc elem - all damage spells cast on you are channeled thru YOU and onto YOUR target which allows anyone to cast all they want on you and land it on the target (allowing you to build aggro) also another idea I had - which could unbalance PvP but ... oh well even VI aint perfect. <p>Garoar Battlebeast Vah Shir Warlord and Officer in Illusion of Fate<BR><img src="http://home.cfl.rr.com/illusionoffate/logo.jpg" width="376" height="256"></a><BR> Did I do that?</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukrazrussian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KrazRussian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/20/02 9:51:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1291.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_atk.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Idea for a new Disc /disc elem</span><hr size=1> please. Dear god, no more discs. If you look at warrior discs now; it's either an 8-second offensive flick with 30 minute reuse that you wish you never used so you could have defensive up. Or, it's defensive; which makes you a 3-minute raid wonder, while lowering your DPS and agro-holding abilities; an ability that I haven't used in a group outside of emergency situations in, well, a while.<br>
<br>
honestly; the fact that warriors are already too much based on time-factor limits. 12 min defensive recycle; what is it 15-min AoE taunt recycle; combine with hte fact that discs are all on the same recycle tables. The fact of the matter is, discs aren't, and shouldn't be the answer. We rely on 3-min prostetics to make us superior tanks compared to others; something we should already be. And prostetic weapons, increasing our dependancy on procs to maintain agro, something we should already be able to do.  <br>
<br>
Please, no more discs. No more once-every-15-min AA abilities. if we're gonna be so heavily dependant on discs and non-permanent AA's, at least havethem work more like spells, in the sense that we are not limited to being able to use them once every XX minutes; but as often as we want until we run out of mana (we don't actually have mana; nor do I think we should; it's more of a metaphor for how i feel discs and non-perma AA's should be based). <p><center><p><font size = 3 colo = "blue"><b>Wilhelmm D'Averam<br>Warlord of the Apocalypse</b></font></p></center>

